Cape Town International Airport has been voted the best airport in Africa. CAPE TOWN - The praise just keeps streaming in for the Mother City. Cape Town International Airport has once again been voted Africa's best airport. READ: Cape Town International Airport is Africa's best The announcement was made at a recent awards ceremony in Mauritius. "We're very proud to announce that Cape Town International Airport scooped the World Travel Award for Africa's leading airport," said Airports Company SA spokesperson Deidre Davids. Table Mountain scooped the title of Africa’s Leading Tourist Attraction at the same awards ceremony